100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 22, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing international disarmament amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to stir public opinion, with various states grappling with enforcement challenges. Meanwhile, reports of severe winter weather across the Midwest raised concerns about agricultural impacts and transportation disruptions.
